   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Uruguay Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Distribution of home disinfection kits and personal hygiene kits</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On January 8 preventive evacuations in Durazno began. The evacuations in Artigas, Bella Union, Salto and Paysand&#xFA; began on January 12. (Northern Zone of the Country):

&#x2022; The departments with greater affectation are Paysand&#xFA; and Salto maintaining a level of continuous flood.
&#x2022; It is reported that Artigas remains affected but at low levels.
&#x2022; According to data provided by the Mixed Technical Commission of Salto Grande (Dam), the Port of Salto will reach a level of 14.90 on January 18. The flood is slow developing, therefore it has not yet reached the most critical point of the flood.
&#x2022; The number of people continues to increase quickly
&#x2022; 1081 people evacuated in shelters
&#x2022; No injured persons are registered
&#x2022; 2 died, one in Rio Negro due to drowning and the other one due to impact of lightning
&#x2022; 3969 displaced persons (official figure)</narrative>
  </description>
